br10.xml<pre><code>&lt;network&gt;
  &lt;name&gt;br10&lt;/name&gt;
  &lt;forward mode='nat'&gt;
    &lt;nat&gt;
      &lt;port start='1024' end='65535'/&gt;
    &lt;/nat&gt;
  &lt;/forward&gt;
  &lt;bridge name='br10' stp='on' delay='0'/&gt;
  &lt;ip address='192.168.72.1' netmask='255.255.255.0'&gt;
    &lt;dhcp&gt;
      &lt;range start='192.168.72.50' end='192.168.72.200'/&gt;
    &lt;/dhcp&gt;
  &lt;/ip&gt;
&lt;/network&gt;
</code></pre> Save this as <code>br10.xml</code> to define the Bridge. <p>Temporarily start the <code>libvirtd</code> service to create the bridge.</p> <pre><code># Start the Service Right now
sudo systemctl start libvirtd.service
# Create the Network Bridge
sudo virsh net-define br10.xml
</code></pre>

bubble_sort.py<pre><code>def bubble_sort(items):
    for i in range(len(items)):
        for j in range(len(items) - 1 - i):
            if items[j] &gt; items[j + 1]:
                items[j], items[j + 1] = items[j + 1], items[j]
</code></pre>
